... Constructive usage of Gematria can be remarkably degraded, and if taken seriously demands greater caution (and scepticism). This experimental process explores attunement of thought (to the Outside, or 'coincidence'), once again confirming or disconfirming inspiration. ...
... In its most faithful application it invokes an external criterion to guide thought. To some, this is sublimely revelatory. It is fine, of course, to prefer a mere hobby. ...

... The most traditional usage of Gematria is to communicate with angels. Many still seek to employ it this way, if at times -- often -- unpersuasively. It is the alternative, hobbyist usage that is novel, and fallen, requiring justification, if justification were needed. ...

... But Gematria is exact, testable, and perfectly reliable, so no extrinsic justification is called for. 
Do what thou wilt shall be the whole of the Law. 
If a hobby is what you want, have a hobby, but such preference is not authoritative for anybody else.
